Text: The value of each URI element in ElectronicAddress element must have a scheme.
The scheme of the value of each URI element in ElectronicAddress element must be either "mailto" or one of ("http" or "https").
Within the element ElectronicAddress there must be at least one URI whose scheme is "mailto" and at least one whose scheme is either "http" or "https".
Within the element ElectronicAddress there must be at least one URI whose scheme is "mailto" and whose xml:lang attribute value is "en".
Within the element ElectronicAddress there should be at least one URI whose scheme is "mailto" and whose xml:lang attribute value is "en" in lower cases.
Within the element ElectronicAddress there must be at least one URI whose scheme is either "http" or "https", and whose xml:lang attribute value is "en".
Within the element ElectronicAddress there should be at least one URI whose scheme is either "http" or "https", and whose xml:lang attribute value is "en" in lower cases.

Cheking order and cardinality of children of $A1 aganist specification.
Cheking attributes of $A1 aganist specification.
Component $A1 MUST be an integer.
There has been an error when trying to parse a purported $A1 component.
There has been an error when trying to parse a $A1 in $A2.
The component $A1 should not be present in $A2. The TLCC will not conduct any check on it.
The component under check is unkown for the TLCC. The TLCC will not conduct any check on it.
The extension $A1 of $A2 component MUST NOT BE set to be critical.
The extension $A1 of $A2 component MUST BE set to be critical.
The component $A1 must contain an $A2.
The X509 certificate must contain a public key.
The sequence of elements corresponding to one digital identity must correspond to the same public key.
If there are several X509 certificates within one digital identity all of them must have the same Subject Name.
Any X509 certificate within one digital identity component must have an attribute O within its SubjectName.
Any X509 certificate within one digital identity component must have the attribute O within its SubjectName equal to the Trust Service Provider's name.

Any X509 certificate within one digital identity component may have the attribute O within its SubjectName equal to the Trust Service Provider's Trade Name and this should be stated in the website pointed by the SchemeServiceDefinitionURI component.
Any X509 certificate within one digital identity component has the attribute O within its SubjectName equal to the Trust Service Provider's name if the comparison is case insensitive.
Any X509 certificate within one digital identity component has the attribute O within its SubjectName equal to the Trust Service Provider's Trade Name if the comparison is case insensitive.

Any X509 certificate within one digital identity component must have the attribute O within its SubjectName equal either to the Trust Service Provider's Name or equal to the Trust Service Provider's Trade Name (in which case this should be stated in the website pointed by the SchemeServiceDefinitionURI component).
The X509 certificate must not be present in the TL as the digital identity of another service of the same type.

The Trusted List MUST NOT contain two equal complete digital identities. A complete digital identity is a tuple formed by: a public key, the type of service owning the public key, and the combination of the following asie extensions: forESignature, forESeal, forWebAuthentication.
The contents of the SubjectKeyIdentifier extension in any X509 certificate within the digital identity have to be correct.
The content of the X509SKI component must be equal to the SubjectKeyIdentifier present in any X509 certificate within the digital identity.

The content of the X509SKI component should be equal to the SubjectKeyIdentifier computed on this X509 certificate if it does not have this extension, using the two methods specified in the RFC 5280 clause 4.2.1.2.
The string representation of a subject name should not include white spaces next to '=' characters, according to RFC 4514.
Any X509SubjectName element shall contain a value equal to the SubjectName of a certificate present in the ServiceDigitalIdentity parent component.

Any X509SubjectName element shall contain a value equal to the subject name of a certificate present in the ServiceDigitalIdentity parent element.A new SubjectName has been found within a X509SubjectName in the Service Digital Identity, different from other(s) found so far. However this may be due to the fact that the conversion of DNs to String is not canonical. Users are kindly asked to review the X509SubjectName and certificate according to the details given here.
The X509Certificate component must not appear in the historical section of a service.
The ds:KeyValue must contain the value of a public key.
This X509 certificate is expired and does appear within one digital identity component present in a section of a service whose status is  granted or recognised at national level.

Please note that all X509 certificates found in the digital identity component are expired while the status of the service is $A1. It is advised to check whether a new certificate should be added or the service status changed.
Index for $A1 is out of range. There are not so many $A2 in the TL.
The value of the xml:lang attribute of $A1 is one of the values for European languages specified in IETF RFC 5646 and in clause E.1 of ETSI TS 119 612.
The value of the xml:lang attribute of $A1 should be one of the values for European languages in lower letters.
The value of the xml:lang attribute of one of the $A1 elements shall be 'en'.
The value of the xml:lang attribute of one of the $A1 elements should be 'en' (in lower letters).
TSLtag MUST be http://uri.etsi.org/19612/TSLTag
TSLVersionIdentifier MUST be 5.
Component TSLSequenceNumber MUST be equal or greater than 1.
The English SchemeName value for an EUMS TL or for the EC List of Trusted Lists MUST be as specified in COMMISSION IMPLEMENTING DECISION (EU) 2015/1505.
For an EUMS Trusted List the SchemeTerritory value MUST be the country code of one of the EU member States.
For the EC List of Trusted Lists the SchemeTerritory value MUST be "EU".
For a list that is neither the EC List of Trusted Lists or one of the EUMS Trusted Lists, the SchemeTerritory value MUST NOT be neither "EU" nor none of the codes of the EUMS.
The difference between NextUpdate and List Issue Date and Time MUST not exceed 6 months
The two first characters of $A1 of $A2 MUST be equal to the code in $A3 element
The two first characters of $A1 of $A2 MUST be equal to the code in $A3 element. They are if case is ignored
The second part of the English $A1 child of $A2 MUST be as specified in CID 2015/1505
The two first characters of $A1 of $A2 MUST be equal to the code in $A3 element. The TSLType indicates that the TL is neither an EUMS TL nor the EC list of Trusted Lists
The two first characters of $A1 of $A2 MUST be equal to the code in $A3 element. The TSLType indicates that the TL is neither an EUMS TL nor the EC list of Trusted Lists
The second part of the English $A1 child of $A2 MUST NOT be as specified in CID 2015/1505
The second part of the English $A1 child of $A2 MUST NOT be as specified in CID 2015/1505
For an EUMS TL the SchemeTypeCommunityRules must contain one URI child whose value is "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/schemerules/EUcommon".
For an EUMS TL the SchemeTypeCommunityRules must contain the URI "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/schemerules/CC" where CC is the territory indicated within the SchemeTerritory component.

For an EUMS TL there MUST be 2 URIs at least, in SchemeTypeCommunityRules, namely: "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/schemerules/EUcommon" and "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/schemerules/"

For an EUMS TL the other legal URI value, apart from the common one, may be either "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/schemerules/CC" (where CC is the value of SchemeTerritory component) or any URI descendant from this value.
In an EUMS TL the multilingual element corresponding to the common URI reference "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/schemerules/EUcommon" MUST have its xml:lang attribute set to value "en".

In the EC List of Trusted Lists the multilingual element corresponding to the URI reference "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/schemerules/EUlistofthelists" MUST have its xml:lang attribute set to value "en".
In an EUMS TL the multilingual element corresponding to the common URI reference value SHOULD have its xml:lang attribute set to value "en" in lower cases.

In the EC List of Trusted Lists the multilingual element corresponding to the URI reference "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/schemerules/EUlistofthelists" SHOULD have its xml:lang attribute set to value "en" in lower cases.
The "TSLLegalNotice" component's value is the mandatory value for an EUMS List as specified in the Official Journal of the European Union.
The "TSLLegalNotice" component whose value is the mandatory value for this type of list as specified in the Official Journal of the European Union, must have its xml:lang attribute set to "en".

The "TSLLegalNotice" component whose value is the mandatory value for this type of list as specified in the Official Journal of the European Union, should have its xml:lang attribute set to "en" in lower cases.

The "TSLLegalNotice" component's value is either the translation to the national language of the mandatory text, or the optional value for an EUMS List as specified in the Official Journal of the European Union.
The value of one of the "TSLLegalNotice" components must be the mandatory value for the EC List of Trusted Lists.
The "TSLLegalNotice" component's value for a non EU list is none of the values specified for EUMS nor the value specified for the EC LoL.
The "TSLPolicy" component component MUST not be present neither in an EUMS list nor in the EC LoL.
The "HistoricalInformationPeriod" component MUST have the value "65535".
In an EUMS TL the OtherTSLPointer child points to the XML EC list of Trusted Lists.
For an EUMS TL, within a pointer pointing to the XML EC LOTL the TSLType of AdditionalInformation in OtherPointerTSL MUST BE "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/TSLType/EUlistofthelists".
For EC list of Trusted Lists the TSLType of AdditionalInformation in one of the pointers in OtherPointerTSL MUST BE "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/TSLType/EUlistofthelists".
For EC list of Trusted Lists the TSLType of AdditionalInformation in all but one of the pointers in OtherPointerTSL MUST BE "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/TSLType/EUgeneric".
The value of an SchemeTerritory child of AdditionalInformation child of one OtherPointerTSL pointing to the EC list of Trusted Lists MUST be "EU".
The value of an SchemeTerritory child of AdditionalInformation child of one OtherPointerTSL pointing to an EUMS TL MUST be the country code of an EUMS
The value of an SchemeTerritory child of AdditionalInformation child of one OtherPointerTSL pointing to the EC list of Trusted Lists SHOULD be "EU".
The value of an SchemeTerritory child of AdditionalInformation child of one OtherPointerTSL pointing to a EUMS TL SHOULD be the country code of an EUMS in lower case.
The certificate in the Pointer to the XML list of lists MUST be the signing certificate for that list as published by the EC.
The Pointer to the XML list of lists MUST contain all the potential signing certificates for that list as published by the EC.
For EC list of Trusted Lists there MUST BE one pointer pointing to the XML EC list of Trusted Lists itself.
For EC list of Trusted Lists there MUST BE one pointer pointing to each EUMS TL.

The ExpiredCertsRevocationInfo Extension MUST be applied to one of the following services: CA (PKC), CA (QC), NationalRootCA-QC, Certificate Status (OCSP and OCSP/QC), Certificate status (CRL and CRL/Q).
The value of Qualifier element MUST be one of the set defined for this component.
The CriteriaList component MUST contain some other child than Description (it MUST contain some criteria).
The value of the name attribute of KeyUsageBit element MUST be one of the set defined by ETSI TS 119 612 v2.1.1.
When Qualifier attribute has the value OIDAsURN then the value of the Identifier MUST be an URN as specified in IETF RFC 3061.

The scheme and authority of the URI element in the TakenOverBy Extension SHOULD BE equal to the scheme and authority of one the following URIS: the URI within the ElectronicAddress of the taking over TSP, the TSPInformationURI of the taking over TSP, the URI within the ElectronicAddress of the Trusted List Scheme Operator, or the SchemeInformationURI of the Trusted List Scheme.
The English part of SchemeOperatorName component of TakenOverBy extension MUST be equal to the English part of SchemeOperatorName in the SchemeInformation section of the Trusted List.

The English part of SchemeOperatorName component of TakenOverBy extension SHOULD be equal to the English part of SchemeOperatorName in the SchemeInformation section of the Trusted List. Differences in cases of some letters have been found
The English part of TSPName component of TakenOverBy extension MUST be equal to the English part of the TSPName of one of the TSPs listed in the Trusted List.

The English part of TSPName component of TakenOverBy extension SHOULD be equal to the English part of the TSPName of one of the TSPs listed in the Trusted List. Differences in cases of some letters have been found

The TL Conformance Checker has not been able to build up the Apache XML Signature element. It will not be possible to check which is the signing certificate and to conduct the cryptographic check of the digital signature value.
One of the ds:Reference elements MUST have an URI set to a value referencing the TrustServiceStatusList that envelopes the signature.
he ds:Reference element referencing the enveloping TrustServiceStatusList MUST contain only ONE ds:Transforms element.
The ds:Transforms child of the ds:Reference element referencing the enveloping TrustServiceStatusList MUST contain TWO ds:Transform elements.

The first ds:Transforms child of the ds:Reference element referencing the enveloping TrustServiceStatusList MUST have the Algorithm attribute set to: 'http://www.w3.org/2000/09/xmldsig#enveloped-signature'.
The second ds:Transforms child of the ds:Reference element referencing the enveloping TrustServiceStatusList MUST have the Algorithm attribute set to: 'http://www.w3.org/2001/10/xml-exc-c14n'.
The canonicalization MUST be set to: 'http://www.w3.org/2001/10/xml-exc-c14n'.
The ds:KeyInfo MUST have only ONE X509Certificate component.
The ds:KeyInfo MUST contain the signing certificate.
The crytpographic verification of ds:SignatureValue with the public key within the signing certificate MUST succeed.
The signing certificate MUST be protected by the signature.
The TL signature MUST be either a XAdES-BES or a XAdES-EPES.
The signing certificate shall be issued by one of the following entities: the TSLO itself, a TSP listed in the TL, or a TSP within the same community.
The Organization attribute of the Subject field MUST match the valule of one of the values of SchemeOperatorName.
The Country attribute of the Subject field MUST match the value of one of the values of SchemeTerritory.
The signing certificate's KeyUsage extension shall have the value digitalSignature or nonRepudiation to the exclusion of any other KeyUsage value.
The signing certificate's ExtendedKeyUsage extension should be present containing the value id-tsl-kp-tslSigning.
The signing certificate's BasicConstraints extension shall indicate CA=false.
The signing certificate shall contain the SubjectKeyIdentifier extension and its value shall be computed with one of the first 2 methods specified in clause 4.2.1.2 of IETF RFC 5280.
The signing certificate of the TL shall be listed in the EC List of Lists.
The signing certificate of the TL shall not be expired.
Component $A1 must have a not empty string as value.
The list of strings must be neither null nor empty.
The value of $A1 must be a not empty string.
The value of $A1 must be a non null string.
TSLtag MUST be "http://uri.etsi.org/19612/TSLTag"
The TL MUST be signed.

The value of ServiceTyeIdentifier in the service information section MUST be one of the starndardized values supporting EU Regulation 910/2014.

When the StatusStartingTime in an historic instance is previous to the entry into force of the EU Regulation 910/2014, then the type of service in the service section MUST be one of the standardized values supporting EC Directive 1999/93/EC.
The ServiceStatus value MUST be a valid value for the EU Regulation 910/2014 starting on 1st July 2016.
The ServiceStatus value MUST be a valid value for the service type.
If the ServiceTypeIdentifier value is "http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/Svctype/NationalRootCA-QC" the TSPServiceDefinitionURI component MUST be present.
The StatusStartingTime may be a time respect the checking time. If it is later than the checking time, it is an announced status change.
The StatusStartingTime MUST be greater than the time present in StatusStartingTime within the most recent ServiceHistoryInstance.
The ServiceType value $A1 and AdditionalServiceInformation extension value(s) MUST be coherent.
The transition between statues MUST be one of the following: from EUDir to EUDir, from EUDir to EUDir or from EUReg to EUReg.
The transition between statues supporting EC Directive 1999/93 MUST be as specified in ETSI TS 119 612v1.2.1.
The transition between statues supporting EU Regulation 910/2014 MUST be as specified in ETSI TS 119 612v2.1.1.
The value of StartusStartingTime in the first service section corresponding to the entry into force of EU Regulation MUST be the string "2016-06-30T22:00:00Z".
The transition of the status MUST be as specified in ETSI TS 119 612v2.1.1 Annex J.

If the previously listed service is qualified by http://uri.etsi.org/TrstSvc/TrustedList/SvcInfoExt/RootCA-QC then this AdditionalServiceInformation component MUST be kept in the posterior service according to Annex J (a) (ii).
If the previously listed service is qualified by one of the qualifiers identified in Annex J (a) (iv) then this qualifier MUST be migrated to the value specified in the aforementioned point.
The migrated service MUST not contain qualifiers that according to Annex J (a) (iv) MUST migrate to different values.
The value of component $A1 must be a valid URI.
The value is a valid URI but likely weird.
The string value of $A1 is a valid URI AFTER TRIMMING IT. No whitespaces should appear neither at the beginning nor at the end.
The URI must not be null.
The URI must reference to some document on the Web.
The SSL context for connecting to a web server through https protocol has failed.
The value of $A1 must be a non empty URI reference.
The list of URIs must be neither null nor empty.
For a EUMS List, the $A1 MUST be "$A2".
For a EC List of Trusted Lists, the $A1 MUST be "$A2".
A $A1's value set to "$A2" indicates that this is a list of a non EUMS.
A $A1's value set to "$A2" indicates that this is a list of lists of an international organization different than EC.

The $A1 value is not registered in the ETSI Identified Organization Domain. It is not possible to asscertain whether it is a list of a non EUMS or a list of lists of an organization different than EC except for the entities involved in the community this list is part.

The $A1 value is registered in the ETSI Identified Organization Domain. ETSI's registry should indicate whether this value corresponds to a list of a non EUMS or a list of lists of an organization different than EC.
The $A1 value must be coherent with the value of the TSLType. The schema rules is unknown as it seems that the country/community is outside the European Union.
The $A1 value must not be neither a value corresponding to an EUMS Trusted List nor a value corresponding to the EC list of lists.
The $A1 value must be the one corresponding to a EUMS Trusted List.
The $A1 value must be the one corresponding to the EC List of Trusted Lists.
